-- Brazil Stock Movers: Grupo Pao de Acucar, Lupatech, Paranapanema
-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 2011-12-15T20:41:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-15/brazil-stock-movers-gol-linhas-aereas-lupatech-paranapanema.html
The following companies had  unusual (IBOV) 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index slid 0.6 percent to 56,331.15.  Cia. Brasileira de Distribuicao Grupo Pao de Acucar  (PCAR4
BS) sank 2.6 percent to 64.49 reais. Brazil’s biggest retailer
was cut to “neutral” from “buy” at Citigroup Inc.  Lupatech SA  (LUPA3 BS) advanced 3.9 percent to 4.74 reais.
Hidro Jet Equipamentos Hidraulicos Ltda. offered to buy
Lupatech’s Microinox-Fundicao Precisao e Usinagem Ltda. unit for
30 million reais ($16.1 million), Lupatech said in a regulatory
filing yesterday.  Paranapanema SA  (PMAM3 BS) gained 3.2 percent to 3.24
reais. The company’s board approved a plan to list the Brazilian
copper smelter in Bovespa’s Novo Mercado, a segment of the
country’s stock exchange with stricter requirements for
disclosure.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in Sao Paulo at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos in New York at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  